title._content: Miss Archdale, English captain, c. 1934, by Sam Hood.

description._content: Betty Archdale captained the English women's cricket team which toured Australia in 1934-35. These were the first international women's test cricket matches ever played. Archdale later emigrated to Australia, eventually becoming headmistress at Abbotsleigh School in Wahroonga. For more information about women's cricket in Australia see Discover Collections - Cricket in Australia www.sl.nsw.gov.au/discover_collections/society_art/cricke...
